libevent: libevent (an event notification library, used by memcached)
libevent: The libevent API provides a mechanism to execute a callback
libevent: function when a specific event occurs on a file descriptor or
libevent: after a timeout has been reached. Furthermore, libevent also
libevent: support callbacks due to signals or regular timeouts. 
libevent: 
libevent: libevent is meant to replace the event loop found in event driven
libevent: network servers. An application just needs to call event_dispatch()
libevent: and then add or remove events dynamically without having to change
libevent: the event loop.
